      • confirmedOrError

        io.reactivex.Observable<Transaction> confirmedOrError(UnresolvedAddress unresolvedAddress,
                                                      java.lang.String transactionHash)
        Returns an observable stream of the transaction of the given transactionHash. This stream is integrated with the status listener. If an error message for the given transaction hash and signer unresolvedAddress occurs while waiting for the confirmed transaction, a TransactionStatusException with the status error is raised. This will help the caller identify errors faster, unlike the regular confirmed method that will just time out.
        Parameters:
        unresolvedAddress - unresolvedAddress we listen when a transaction is in confirmed state
        transactionHash - the expected transaction hash
        Returns:
        an observable stream of Transaction with given transaction hash and state confirmed.

                                                                          java.lang.String transactionHash)
        Return an observable of AggregateTransaction for an specific unresolvedAddress and transcation hash. Each time an aggregate bonded transaction is announced, it emits a new AggregateTransaction in the event stream. If an error message for the given transaction hash and signer unresolvedAddress occurs while waiting for the confirmed transaction, a TransactionStatusException with the status error is raised. This will help the caller identify errors faster, unlike the regular confirmed method that will just time out.
        Parameters:
        unresolvedAddress - unresolvedAddress we listen when a transaction with missing signatures state.
        transactionHash - the expected transaction hash
        Returns:
        an observable stream of AggregateTransaction with missing signatures state

      • getAllMultisigAddressesAndAliases

        io.reactivex.Observable<java.util.Set<UnresolvedAddress>> getAllMultisigAddressesAndAliases(UnresolvedAddress unresolvedAddress)
        Helper method to return all the known cosigners and it's aliases of a given account. The list includes the aliases of the multisig account.

        You can pipe this method to listen to everything related to an address.

        Parameters:
        unresolvedAddress - the account, most likely a multisig
        Returns:
        a set of all known aliases and addresses of a multisig and its cosignatures

      • getAllAddressesAndAliases

        io.reactivex.Observable<java.util.Set<UnresolvedAddress>> getAllAddressesAndAliases(UnresolvedAddress unresolvedAddress)
        Helper method to return all the known aliases of a given address. The list includes the original address.

        You can pipe this method to listen to everything related to an address.

        Parameters:
        unresolvedAddress - the account
        Returns:
        a set of all known aliases and addresses of the account.

      • subscribeMultipleAddresses

        <T> io.reactivex.Observable<ListenerMessage<T>> subscribeMultipleAddresses(ListenerChannel channel,
                                                                           java.util.Set<UnresolvedAddress> unresolvedAddresses,
                                                                           java.lang.String transactionHash,
                                                                           boolean orError)
        This method allows you to subscribes to multiple unresolved addresses as the same time.

        This is ideal for:

        1) When you have multiple aliases of a given account.

        2) When you want to subscribe to the cosigners and its aliases.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the payload, most of the time it will be Transaction
        Parameters:
        channel - the channel.
        unresolvedAddresses - the unresolved address.
        transactionHash - the transaction hash
        orError - do you want to raise an error when a status for the given hash is received?
        Returns:
        the observable of the payload.
